Describe a person you know who is from a different culture
- who he/she is
- where he/she is from
- how you met this person
- explain how you feel about this person

To be honest, I haven’t had many opportunities to interact with people from different cultures, as I’ve mostly been surrounded by Vietnamese people. However, one person who stands out is my English teacher, Rob, who is from England.

I first met him about six months ago when I enrolled in an IELTS course at a local language center, where he was the speaking instructor. He’s probably in his 30s and has a tall, well-built figure. He also has blonde hair and blue eyes, which gives him a very typical Western appearance.

What impressed me the most about him wasn’t just his appearance, but his confidence and teaching ability. From the very first lesson, he demonstrated a deep understanding of the IELTS exam and helped us clear up many common misconceptions. He also encouraged us to speak more naturally, rather than relying on memorized or overly formal language.

Another quality I really admire is his teaching style. His accent is clear and easy to understand, and he creates a very supportive learning environment. He always motivates students to speak up and reassures us that making mistakes is a natural part of the learning process. Thanks to him, I’ve become much more confident in expressing myself in English.

Overall, I feel very fortunate to have learned from someone like him. Not only has he helped me improve my English skills, but he has also given me valuable insights into a different culture, which I find both interesting and inspiring.
